=\nFour players were sold by the club during the season with a public total of at least \u00a380,000 (some figures unavailable).\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%\"\n|-\n! Date !! Player !! To !! Fee\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} September 1987 || {{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|John|Holt|John Holt (footballer, born 1956)}} || [[Dunfermline Athletic F.C.|Dunfermline]] || Unknown<ref name=\"kirkwood\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Holt%20J.htm|title=Player A to Z: John Holt|publisher=Glenrothes Arabs|accessdate=6 February 2008|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081015114526/http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Holt%20J.htm |archivedate = 15 October 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} September 1987 || {{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Billy|Kirkwood}} || [[Dunfermline Athletic F.C.|Dunfermline]] || Unknown<ref name=\"autogenerated3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Kirkwood%20B.htm|title=Player A to Z: Billy Kirkwood|publisher=Glenrothes Arabs|accessdate=6 February 2008|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080828225920/http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Kirkwood%20B.htm |archivedate = 28 August 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| 11 February 1988 || {{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Alan|Irvine|Alan Irvine (footballer born 1962)}} || [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] || \u00a30,080,000<ref name=\"irvine2\"/>\n|-\n| {{0}}{{0}} February 1988 || {{flagicon|SCO}} {{sortname|Paul|Kinnaird}} || [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] || Unknown<ref name=\"kinnaird\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/Player%20a-z/Kinnaird%20P.htm|title=Player A to Z: Paul Kinnaird|publisher=Glenrothes Arabs|accessdate=6 February 2008}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Playing kit==\n{| style=\"border:0;\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _blackline\n| pattern_b  = _vneckblack\n| pattern_ra = _blackline\n| leftarm    = EE7700\n| body       = EE7700\n| rightarm   = EE7700\n| shorts     = 000000\n| socks      = EE7700\n| title      = Home<br />colours\n}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _blackline\n| pattern_b  = _vneckblack\n| pattern_ra = _blackline\n| leftarm    = FFFFFF\n| body       = FFFFFF\n| rightarm   = FFFFFF\n| shorts     = 000000\n| socks      = FFFFFF\n| title      = Away<br />colours\n}}\n|}\nThe jerseys were sponsored by [[Belhaven Brewery|Belhaven Beers]] for the first time.\n\n==See also==\n*[[1987\u201388 in Scottish football]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080703194339/http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/History/1980s/1987-88/87-88page.htm Glenrothes Arabs 1987\u201388 season review]\n\n{{Dundee United F.C.}}\n{{Dundee United F.C. seasons}}\n{{1987-88 in Scottish football}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dundee United F.C. Season 1987-88}}\n[[Category:Dundee United F.C. seasons|1987-88]]\n[[Category:Scottish football clubs 1987\u201388 season]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox Football club season\n| club = [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n| logo = [[File:Dufc.gif]]\n| season = 1987\u201388\n| manager = [[Jim McLean]]\n| chairman = George Fox\n| league = [[Scottish Football League Premier Division|Scottish Premier Division]]\n| league result = 5th ([[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]])<br />W16 D15 L13 F54 A47 P47\n| cup1 = [[Tennent's]] [[Scottish Cup]]| cup1 result = Runners-up\n| cup2 = [[Scottish League Cup|Skol Cup]] | cup2 result = Quarter-finals\n| cup3 = [[UEFA Cup]] | cup3 result = Second round\n| league topscorer = [[Iain Ferguson]] (11)\n| season topscorer = [[Iain Ferguson]] (16)\n| highest attendance = 20,846 vs [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] (27 February)\n| lowest attendance = 5,703 vs [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] (12 December)\n| prevseason = [[1986\u201387 Dundee United F.C. season|1986\u201387]]\n| nextseason = [[1988\u201389 Dundee United F.C. season|1988\u201389]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1987\u201388 season''' was the 79th year of [[association football|football]] played by [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]], and covers the period from 1 July 1987 to 30 June 1988. United finished in fifth place, securing [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]] football for the following season, despite their [[Scottish Cup]] final defeat to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] (Celtic qualified for European competition as league winners).\n\n==Match results==\nDundee United played a total of 60 competitive matches during the 1987\u201388 season.<ref name=\"results\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arabarchive.co.uk/matches.php?|title=Match results 1987/1988|work=Arab Archive|accessdate=14 November 2016}}</ref> The team finished fifth in the [[Scottish Premier Division]].\n\nIn the cup competitions, United lost in the final of the [[Scottish Cup]] to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] and lost in the [[Scottish League Cup|Skol Cup]] quarter-finals to rivals [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]. [[Czechoslovakia]]n side [[FC V\u00edtkovice|V\u00edtkovice]] ensured United wouldn't repeat last season's [[UEFA Cup]] run, beating them in the second round.\n\n===Legend===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#efe;\"|<small>Win</small>\n| style=\"background:#ffe;\"|<small>Draw</small>\n| style=\"background:#fee;\"|<small>Loss</small>\n|}\n\nAll results are written with Dundee United's score first.\n\n===Premier Division===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}8 August 1987 ||{{left}}[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||[[Ibrox Stadium|A]]||1\u20131||39,120||{{left}}[[Dave Beaumont|Beaumont]]\n|- style=\"background:#ffe;\"\n| {{left}}12 August 1987 ||{{left}}[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||[[Tannadice Park|H]]||1\u20131||6,633||{{left}}[[Ian Redford|Redford]]\n|- style=\"background:#ef