eston]]|pos=MF|nat=Scotland|2|0|0|0|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Ian Redford]]|pos=MF|nat=Scotland|25|6|8|2|3|0|2|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Iain Ferguson]]|pos=FW|nat=Scotland|38|11|8|2|3|2|3|1}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Hamish French]]|pos=FW|nat=Scotland|20|3|5|1|0|0|1|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Kevin Gallacher]]|pos=FW|nat=Scotland|26|3|8|3|1|2|1|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Alan Irvine (footballer born 1962)|Alan Irvine]]|pos=FW|nat=Scotland|7|0|0|0|1|0|0|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Mixu Paatelainen]]|pos=FW|nat=Finland|19|9|8|2|0|0|0|0}}\n{{Extended football squad player|no=|name=[[Paul Sturrock]]|pos=FW|nat=Scotland|9|3|0|0|3|2|3|2}}\n|}\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Goalscorers===\nUnited had 19 players score with the team scoring 83 goals in total. The top goalscorer was [[Iain Ferguson]], who finished the season with 16 goals.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dirtyarab.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/History/1987s/1987-88/87-88page.htm|title=1987\u201388|work=Glenrothes Arabs|accessdate=6 February 2008}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!Name!!League!!Cups!!Total\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Iain|Ferguson}}||11||5||{{goal}} '''16'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Mixu|Paatelainen}}||9||2||{{goal}} '''11'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Ian|Redford}}||6||2||{{goal}} {{0}}'''8'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Paul|Sturrock}}||3||4||{{goal}} {{0}}'''7'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Kevin|Gallacher}}||3||3||{{goal}} {{0}}'''6'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|John|Clark|John Clark (footballer born 1964)}}||3||2||{{goal}} {{0}}'''5'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Eamonn|Bannon}}||1||4||{{goal}} {{0}}'''5'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Hamish|French}}||3||1||{{goal}} {{0}}'''4'''\n|-\n|{{left}}{{sortname|Alan|Irvine|Alan Irvine (footballer born 1958)}}||2||2|