 2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40761&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20prodlou%C5%BEen%C3%AD%20omezen%C3%AD%20pohybu%20osob.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15190/2020-5/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"curfew 10 April\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40922&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20z%C3%A1kaz%20voln%C3%A9ho%20pohybu%20osob,%20s%20vyjimkami.pdf |title=Data |publisher=www.mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''Schools suspended.'''}}\n| All pupils and students banned from personally attending classes (including university lectures). Staff may continue to work and assign homework for students.\n\nKindergartens and creches remain open.\n| 10 March 2020\n| From 11 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| From 13 March onwards ban extended to include also extracurricular/after school activities.\n\nFrom 20 April onwards students may attend university exams with max 5 persons present, may also attend clinical education or practical/laboratory education with max 5 persons present. \n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10676/2020-1/MIN/KAN (11\u201313 March 2020)<ref name=\"100 people ban\"/>\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 201/2020 Coll. (from 13 March onwards)<ref name=\"all school banned\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/Opatreni-o-zakazu-skolni-dochazky--vzdelavacich-a-volnocasovych-aktivit-ve-skolstvi_1.pdf |title=Usenesni |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 16184/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40951&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20uzav%C5%99en%C3%AD%20%C5%A1kol%20a%20%C5%A1kolsk%C3%BDch%20za%C5%99%C3%ADzen%C3%AD,%20s%20%C3%BA%